Real-Life Analogy
CBOW
I ____ pizza

Using the surrounding words:

I
pizza

Predict:

love
Skip-Gram

Given only:

love

Predict the surrounding words:

I
pizza

=============

Skip-Gram is a Word2Vec model that uses a target word as input and predicts the surrounding context words
within a specified window size. It creates multiple target–context training pairs, learns word 
embeddings using a neural network, and is particularly effective at learning representations for rare words.

=================

CBOW
Context Words
      ↓
Predict Target Word

Example:

Input : quick, brown, jumps, over
Output: fox
Skip-Gram
Target Word
      ↓
Predict Context Words

Example:

Input : fox
Output: quick, brown, jumps, over

================


CBOW = Many → One (Many context words predict one target word)
Skip-Gram = One → Many (One target word predicts many context words)







